    public static final String CONST_GAL_FAQ_CONTENT1 ="With Galaxy Credentials, developers are able to build a Web3 Decentralised ID system that not only gives you a multi-chain identity but also lets others know more about you through your credentials and past achievements. Projects like Cyberconnect, Unipass, and Salad Venture are already utilising Galaxy Credentials within their products.";
    public static final String CONST_GAL_FAQ_CONTENT2 ="Curators will earn revenue streams when the data they curate is utilised in Galaxy’s Application Modules, Credential Oracle Engine, and Credential API. This creates a network effect because as more credential data flows into the system, the more developers will onboard to utilise such data, and in turn incentivize more curators to contribute credentials.";
    public static final String CONST_GAL_FAQ_CONTENT3 ="Galxe is a Chain-Agnostic Credential Network. Their infrastructure is currently aggregating credentials through seven different chains (Ethereum, BNB Chain, Polygon, Solana, Fantom, Arbitrum, Avalanche), and has integrated multiple sources such as Twitter, Discord, and Github. Galxe currently has more than 1500 credential data sets curated in the network, covering more than 4 million wallet addresses in Web3.";

